name: Paul Skenes
summary: Paul Skenes, the Pittsburgh Pirates' highly touted pitching prospect, is set to make his long-awaited Major League Baseball debut on Saturday. The 6-foot-6, 230-pound left-hander has been ranked among the top three prospects in all of baseball and is considered one of the most promising young arms in the game. Skenes was drafted by the Pirates with the 16th overall pick in the 2023 MLB Draft and has quickly risen through the organization's minor league system. He has a fastball that can reach the upper 90s, along with a sharp slider and developing changeup. The Pirates are expected to exercise caution with Skenes' workload as he makes the transition to the majors, but they believe he has the potential to be a future ace.
